{"title":"Lachlan Morton to ride all 21 Stages of Tour de France plus transfers in his Alt Tour","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/28/lachlan-morton-to-ride-all-21-stages-of-tour-de-france-plus-transfers-in-his-alt-tour/","date":1624877942000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Each team in the Tour de France has eight riders, right? Until now. Sort of. Lachlan Morton is joining the EF Education Nippo Pro Cycling team as the ninth rider, riding his Alt Tour to the Champs-Élysées. He will be riding all 21 Stages and every single transfer, unsupported, in a bid to beat the Peloton to Paris.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/USm-y6-X0SY?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" ezoid=\"0.21518964250393458\"></iframe></span></p><p>Lachlan set off on this incredible solo mission on Saturday, shortly after the Peloton’s Grand Départ from Brest, Northern France. While the Tour de France cyclists will be riding 3,383 km with 42,200 m elevation, Lachlan’s Alt Tour is a 5,510 km with 65,500 m of elevation gain.&nbsp;</p><figure id=\"attachment_263135\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-263135\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france.jpg\" alt=\"lachlan morton riding tour de france plus transfers unsupported alt tour\" width=\"1200\" height=\"832\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.a