28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-800x555.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-120x83.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-768x532.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-218x150.jpg 218w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-696x483.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-1068x740.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-606x420.jpg 606w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064127/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-100x70.jpg 100w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-263135\">Photo Credit: Grubers</figcaption></figure><p>What’s more, Lachlan will be doing this entirely self-supported. No mechanic. No team bus. No team mates to shelter behind. And… <em>no rest days</em>. He estimates that he’ll need to put in 238 hours of riding over the 23 days in order to beat the Peloton to Paris. That’s an average of just over 10 hours in the saddle, every single day.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064133/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-world-bicycle-relief.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/28064133/lachlan-morton-alt-tour-de-france-world-bicycle-relief.jpg\" alt=\"lachlan morton alt tour route\" width=\"1200\" height=\"848\" dat